<a id="phase-4"></a>
## Phase 4: Code Quality Review

### 4.1 Major Code Quality Issues

| # | Issue | Location | Severity |
|---|---|---|---|
| Q1 | **Route files contain 500–868 lines of business logic** (fat controllers) | [article.routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/article.routes.ts) (551 lines), [rss.routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/rss.routes.ts) (868 lines) | High |
| Q2 | **`any` type used extensively** on frontend | RSS page (lines 87, 100, 579), dashboard activity list | Medium |
| Q3 | **Duplicated validation schemas** — Zod schemas defined inside route files AND in validators/ | rss.routes.ts duplicates `createSourceSchema` instead of importing from validators | Medium |
| Q4 | **Test files exist but are minimal** — only 2 test files in `server/src/tests/` | tests/ directory | High |
| Q5 | **Unused imports and utility files** — `check-image.ts`, `check-sources.ts`, `dump_categories.ts` in root | Server root | Low |
| Q6 | **Magic numbers scattered** — `300000` server timeout, `5 * 60 * 1000` cache TTL, `30` cleanup days | Multiple files | Medium |
| Q7 | **Inconsistent error handling** — some use `try/catch` with `next(error)`, some use `Promise.catch(() => {})` | Multiple services | Medium |
| Q8 | **Frontend services import pattern inconsistent** — some via barrel `index.ts`, some direct imports | `src/services/` | Low |

### 4.2 Naming Convention Issues

- `rSSSource` / `rSSArticle` / `rSSFeed` — Prisma auto-generates awkward camelCase from uppercase model names
- Frontend uses both `showError` and `error` for toast error display
- Backend and frontend both have `automation.service.ts` with different contents

