<a id="phase-5"></a>
## Phase 5: Architecture Review

### 5.1 Architectural Issues

| # | Issue | Impact | Severity |
|---|---|---|---|
| A1 | **No service layer on backend** — business logic lives in route handlers | Routes are untestable, unreusable, 500+ lines each | **Critical** |
| A2 | **Tight coupling between scheduler and services** — scheduler directly calls service functions | Cannot swap implementations, no DI | Medium |
| A3 | **Singleton Prisma client exported from index.ts** — circular dependency risk | `server/src/index.ts` exports `prisma`, services import it | Medium |
| A4 | **No queue system** — social posting, AI rewriting, and scraping all use `node-cron` polling | No backpressure, no retry with exponential backoff | High |
| A5 | **WhatsApp service auto-initializes via import side-effect** | `import './services/whatsapp.service.js'` at server start | Medium |
| A6 | **No API versioning** — all routes under `/api/*` | Breaking changes affect all clients simultaneously | Medium |
| A7 | **Frontend and backend share no types** — types duplicated between packages | Risk of schema drift | Medium |

### 5.2 Pipeline Architecture Issues

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["RSS Fetch (cron 15min)"] --> B["Store RSSArticle"]
    B --> C["Scrape Queue (cron 5min)"]
    C --> D["Admin Approves"]
    D --> E["Automation Pipeline"]
    E --> F["AI Rewrite (Ollama)"]
    F --> G["Publish Article"]
    G --> H["Social Post"]
    
    style F fill:#ff6b6b,color:white
    style H fill:#ff6b6b,color:white
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **AI rewriting (F) blocks the pipeline** — if Ollama is slow or unavailable, the entire automation queue stalls. There is no timeout, no fallback, and the server timeout is set to 5 minutes globally.

> [!WARNING]
> **Social posting (H) has no dead-letter queue** — failed posts are marked FAILED with no automatic retry.

### 5.3 Recommendations

1. **Extract route business logic into service classes** with proper error typing
2. **Implement BullMQ** (or similar) backed by Redis for: AI rewriting, image processing, social posting
3. **Create a shared types package** between frontend and backend
4. **Add API versioning** (`/api/v1/...`)
5. **Use dependency injection** via constructor parameters instead of direct imports

---

<a id="phase-6"></a>
## Phase 6: Security Review

### 6.1 Critical Security Vulnerabilities

| # | Vulnerability | File | Severity |
|---|---|---|---|
| S1 | **JWT tokens stored in localStorage** — vulnerable to XSS | [api.ts:32-33](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/src/services/api.ts) | **Critical** |
| S2 | **No CSRF protection** — API relies solely on Bearer tokens | [app.ts](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/app.ts) | High |
| S3 | **Refresh token stored in DB unhashed** in login flow, hashed in refresh flow — **inconsistent!** | [auth.routes.ts:195-199](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/auth.routes.ts) vs [auth.routes.ts:287](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/routes/auth.routes.ts) | **Critical** |
| S4 | **CORS allows 4 origins including localhost** in production | [app.ts:44-47](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/src/app.ts) | High |
| S5 | **`server/.env` file present in working directory** (not just `.env.example`) | [server/.env](file:///c:/Users/MahmoodCenter/Desktop/news-platform-next/server/.env) | **Critical** |
| S6 | **No input sanitization for HTML content** — articles store raw HTML in `content` field | article.routes.ts create/update | High |
| S7 | **`trust proxy` set to 1** without hardening — allows header spoofing behind misconfigured proxies | app.ts:35 | Medium |
| S8 | **Static file serving allows directory traversal** via `/uploads/` path | app.ts:56-57 | Medium |
| S9 | **WhatsApp auth state stored on filesystem** with no encryption | whatsapp.service.ts | Medium |
| S10 | **No permission check on article views** — any authenticated user can read draft articles by knowing the ID/slug | article.routes.ts:238-242 | Medium |

### 6.2 Authentication & Authorization Issues

| # | Issue | Details |
|---|---|---|
| S11 | **Role-based access is too coarse** — only 4 roles (ADMIN, EDITOR, JOURNALIST, READER) with no granular permissions | middleware/auth.ts |
| S12 | **`optionalAuth` does NOT verify user is active** — stale tokens pass through | middleware/auth.ts:85-96 |
| S13 | **No account lockout** after failed login attempts (rate limiter is per-IP, not per-account) | rateLimiter.ts |
| S14 | **Social login creates account with no email verification** | auth.routes.ts Google/Facebook flows |
| S15 | **Refresh token comparison uses `findFirst` on raw token in login** but `hashToken` in refresh — **token can be stolen** | auth.routes.ts |

### 6.3 Recommendations

1. **Move tokens to HTTP-only, Secure, SameSite=Strict cookies**
2. **Hash ALL refresh tokens before storing** (fix the inconsistency)
3. **Add DOMPurify** or equivalent HTML sanitizer for article content
4. **Restrict CORS** in production to only the production frontend domain
5. **Add `.env` to `.gitignore`** and verify it's not committed
6. **Implement RBAC** with granular permission sets per resource type
7. **Add account-level lockout** after N failed attempts

