<a id="phase-7"></a>
## Phase 7: Performance Analysis

### 7.1 Database Query Issues

| # | Issue | File | Severity |
|---|---|---|---|
| P1 | **N+1 query in sources list** — each source loads all feeds with all categories | rss.routes.ts GET /sources | High |
| P2 | **No pagination on many admin lists** — categories, users loaded fully | category.routes.ts, user.routes.ts | Medium |
| P3 | **Full-text search uses `contains`** instead of MySQL FULLTEXT index | article.routes.ts search query | High |
| P4 | **View count increment hits Redis on EVERY article read** | article.routes.ts view endpoint | Medium |
| P5 | **`fetchAllActiveFeeds` fetches ALL feeds simultaneously** with `Promise.allSettled` — no concurrency limit | rss.service.ts | High |
| P6 | **Image processing (Sharp) runs in the main event loop** | imageProcessor.ts, rss.service.ts | High |

### 7.2 Caching Analysis

| What's Cached | TTL | Cache Key | ✅/❌ |
|---|---|---|---|
| Featured articles | Exists | `featured:{limit}` | ✅ |
| Breaking news | Exists | `breaking:{limit}` | ✅ |
| Article view counts | Flushed every 5 min | `views:{id}` | ✅ |
| RSS feed results | **Not cached** | — | ❌ |
| Category list | **Not cached** | — | ❌ |
| Admin dashboard stats | Client-side 5min stale | — | ⚠️ |
| RSS articles list | **Not cached** | — | ❌ |

### 7.3 Recommendations

1. **Add `p-limit` to RSS fetching** — limit concurrent feeds to 3-5 (the dependency is already installed!)
2. **Use MySQL FULLTEXT** for search queries (already configured in schema but not used in route)
3. **Cache category list** in Redis — rarely changes
4. **Move image processing to a worker thread** or background job
5. **Add cursor-based pagination** for large lists

---

<a id="phase-8"></a>
## Phase 8: Database Design Review

### 8.1 Schema Issues

| # | Issue | Table/Field | Severity |
|---|---|---|---|
| D1 | **No `deletedAt` soft-delete field** on any table | All models | High |
| D2 | **Redundant AI rewrite fields** on BOTH `RSSArticle` AND `AutomationQueue` | `rewrittenTitle` on RSSArticle AND `aiRewrittenTitle` on AutomationQueue | Medium |
| D3 | **`AutomationQueue.createdArticleId` is a plain String** — not a foreign key relation | schema.prisma:354 | Medium |
| D4 | **`SocialPlatform` enum missing** WHATSAPP — only has FACEBOOK, TELEGRAM, TWITTER | schema.prisma:334-338 | Medium |
| D5 | **`RefreshToken` has no relation to User model** | schema.prisma:199-208 | Low |
| D6 | **Single `socialPlatform` field** on AutomationQueue — can't track multi-platform posting | schema.prisma:358 | High |
| D7 | **`Media` model has no relation to Articles** — orphaned uploads | schema.prisma:166-178 | Medium |
| D8 | **No index on `Article.publishedAt`** standalone (only composite with status) | schema.prisma | Low |

### 8.2 Data Integrity Risks

- **User cascade delete destroys articles** — no soft-delete, no reassignment
- **RSS source cascade delete** removes ALL feeds AND all articles through cascade chain
- **No unique constraint on RSS article `sourceUrl`** — duplicates possible from different feeds
- **`titleHash`** is nullable — duplicate detection only works when hash is computed

### 8.3 Recommendations

1. **Add `deletedAt` to User, Article, RSSArticle, Category** 
2. **Create a `SocialPost` junction table** for multi-platform tracking per article
3. **Make `createdArticleId` a proper FK** with relation
4. **Add WHATSAPP to SocialPlatform enum**
5. **Remove duplicate AI fields** from RSSArticle (keep only on AutomationQueue)
6. **Add Media-Article relation** to track which images belong to which articles

