<a id="phase-10"></a>
## Phase 10: Consolidated Issue Register

### Summary by Severity

| Severity | Count |
|---|---|
| 🔴 Critical | 5 |
| 🟠 High | 16 |
| 🟡 Medium | 18 |
| 🟢 Low | 6 |
| **Total** | **45** |

### Top 10 Priority Issues

| # | Type | Issue | Impact | Fix Effort |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Security | **JWT in localStorage** (S1) | XSS can steal all user sessions | Medium |
| 2 | Security | **Refresh token hashing inconsistency** (S3) | Token theft possible | Low |
| 3 | Logic | **User cascade delete destroys articles** (B3) | Permanent data loss | Low |
| 4 | Security | **`.env` file in server directory** (S5) | Credential exposure if repo is public | Immediate |
| 5 | Architecture | **No service layer — fat routes** (A1) | Untestable, unmaintainable | High |
| 6 | Logic | **No idempotency in automation pipeline** (B7) | Duplicate articles created | Medium |
| 7 | Security | **No HTML sanitization on article content** (S6) | Stored XSS attacks | Low |
| 8 | Performance | **RSS feeds fetched without concurrency limit** (P5) | Server overwhelm with many feeds | Low |
| 9 | Logic | **Social posts auto-completed without posting** (B6) | Articles not actually shared | Low |
| 10 | Database | **No soft-delete anywhere** (D1) | Irreversible data destruction | Medium |

### Quick Wins (Low Effort, High Impact)

1. ✅ Add `server/.env` to `.gitignore` → **prevents credential leak**
2. ✅ Hash refresh tokens consistently → **fixes token theft vulnerability**
3. ✅ Change `User` to `onDelete: SetNull` on Article relation → **prevents data loss**
4. ✅ Add `p-limit(5)` to `fetchAllActiveFeeds` → **prevents server overwhelm** (package already installed)
5. ✅ Add DOMPurify to article content creation → **prevents stored XSS**
6. ✅ Fix social media scheduler to actually check delivery → **ensures content reaches channels**
7. ✅ Restrict CORS to production domain only via env variable → **prevents unauthorized API access**

---

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This audit identified **5 critical** and **16 high-severity** issues. The most urgent are the security vulnerabilities (S1, S3, S5, S6) and data integrity risks (B3, B7). I recommend addressing the **Quick Wins** immediately, then proceeding to architectural refactoring (extracting service layer, implementing proper queue system) as a phased improvement plan.
